description:
&lt;p&gt;The Queen Victoria Hospital Perioperative team pride ourselves on being supportive and friendly with a long history of clinical excellence. We are looking for individuals who are passionate and driven by patient centred care. At the QVH we strive for excellence and are in a position to support individuals with the same passion and driving force. Joining the team you will find a supportive network of practitioners, in which you will become an integral member of the Multidisciplinary team in this acute patient setting. Admission and Discharge experience is desirable but not essential. Opportunities to develop are available within the perioperative environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a specialist hospital patients will be attending for the following surgery:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Major head and neck reconstructive surgery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maxillofacial Surgery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ENT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plastic Surgery including major reconstruction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hand Surgery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ophthalmics including corneal grafts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Burns for reconstructive surgery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trauma&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We care about your professional development; support is available to attend courses, develop your career and develop within the speciality with the opportunity to progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
